  "prompt": "What can I do with an expired passport?",
  "response": "Here are some things you can do with an expired passport:\n\n1. Keep it as a personal document/memento\n- Retain for personal records\n- Store with other important documents\n\n2. Use for identification purposes (limited)\n- Proof of citizenship\n- Verify previous identity or travel history\n- Some forms of secondary identification\n\n3. Official processes\n- Submit with passport renewal application\n- Include as supporting documentation for certain government forms\n\n4. Proper disposal\n- Physically destroy/shred the passport\n- Cut through the photo and personal information page\n- Do not simply throw away intact\n\n5. Cannot use for\n- International travel\n- Entry/exit from countries\n- Boarding flights\n- As a primary form of current government ID\n\n6. Replacement options\n- Renew at passport agency\n- Apply for a new passport\n- Follow current passport application procedures\n\nImportant: Always check current regulations with your specific government passport authority for the most up-to-date guidance.",
